<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-18252] BridgeExceptionHandlerToErrorHandler with OnCompletion prevents processing Exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18252</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using BridgeExceptionHandlerToErrorHandler together with OnCompletion prevents to process the Exception because it temporarily gets removed from exchange and there is no other reference available. JavaDoc of OnCompletionProcessor mentions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;the caused exception is stored as a property (Exchange.EXCEPTION_CAUGHT) on the exchange
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Might be a possible solution to be set in BridgeExceptionHandlerToErrorHandler &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Small test case to verify, see log of missing Exception. (logging null value!)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
